{
  "_comment": [
    "Pre-tiling merge rules for COD (DRC) layers.",
    "Each key under 'merges' is the output path relative to scratch_dir.",
    "Inputs are listed in order — the first entry's schema wins for column types",
    "in UNION ALL BY NAME, so the richer v8_0 source should always be listed first.",
    "IT rows receive NULL for v8_0-only columns (OBJECTID, source_acronym, etc.).",
    "",
    "Field note: v8_0 files may have a 'precision_' column (trailing underscore from",
    "GDAL reserved-word escaping) while IT files use 'precision'. UNION ALL BY NAME",
    "treats these as two distinct columns; both appear in the merged output. MapLibre",
    "style expressions should coalesce: [\"coalesce\", [\"get\", \"precision_\"], [\"get\", \"precision\"]].",
    "",
    "To add a new data source append another entry to the relevant 'inputs' list.",
    "To add a new layer, add a new key to 'merges'."
  ],
